description: Our 4th monthly compilation for Comixology of Aces Weekly - the award-winning on-screen comic art magazine featuring some of the world's finest creators of comic art. Published by David Lloyd, the guy who brought you V For Vendetta.
name: Volume 04

description:
The Legend of the Chupacabra

Billy the 9-year-old Space Captain and his alien friends Phil and Gil are back in a second adventure. This time the boys are camping in the pickleton wilderness and they're not alone...
name: The Legend of the Chupacabra

volume.name: The Adventures of a 4th Grade Space Captain

description: Evil Angelica is out. Government operatives have their sights on their rogue cyborg. George and his friends are in the crossfire, and tensions are stretched to the breaking point. In order to survive the military onslaught without, a small circle of teenagers, some more cybernetic than others, will have to fight against the demons within, confront old grievances, and stop being so damn self absorbed all the time. Plus more Angelica back story! It's the thrilling penultimate issue!

Cyg City Blues

The year: 2062. Reclusive genius and technopath Argent Starr, is on a collision course with destiny. He must recover a stolen world-destroying alien weapon and protect Earth. His team; the fetching, fearless bodyguard Mrs. Jaxon Thorne, and a trouble-making, brain-enhanced, Spanglish-speaking black cat named Specter. The trio are plunged into a galactic sci-noir adventure filled with sabotage, assassins, sex, drugs, high-stakes gambling, spies, magic and the galactic mob.

Is the fate of Earth really in the hands of a half-alien hero scientist, a female sniper, and a talking cat?
name: Cyg City Blues

volume.name: Argent Starr: Tales From the Archives

description: Dean tries rescuing Astrid's stuff from her car as the tide washes it away, but a creepy underwater encounter scares him off, prompting Gabi to tell more of her own story. No one has patience for her digressions, but what they see as the sun sets proves her stories might be true after all. Hopefully they'll heed Jorge's warnings to "remember the wind dimensions."
The Dynamic Duo is trapped in the Widow's deadly web. And the only person who might be able to help them is--the Penguin? Things look grim.
name: Chapter Forty-Three

description:
Join Dennis the Menace, Minnie the Minx and the Bash Street Kids in a riot of jokes, pranks and laughs! The Beano is the only place to keep up with the awesome adventures of the Menace Squad every week!

That's not all...

  • Mischief is a piece of cake for Minnie in the Great Beanotown Bake-Off!
  • Go wild in a brand new story - Beanotown Zoo!
  • Make a mini bow and arrow out of household junk!
  • Win SpongeBob prizes!

Plus... The Bash Street Kids meet Jaws, Tricky Dicky takes you on a grand prix of pranks and much, much more!

After the US Military takes aggressive action, directly attacking Hurricane Brandon, things go from bad to worse. Meanwhile, Cale Isaacs, the man behind the weather control device, fights an ugly and more personal battle in the shadow of Wyoming's Devil's Tower.

Featuring Artwork by Dennis Calero (X-MEN: NOIR).

Note: The digital edition (9/21/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Over time Jackies changes are causing more and more problems in his life. Bad enough that Kathies brother Ron knows his secret, the federals also get to know that something is going on.

And who is this strange guy that makes his life so fucking complicated?

ONE COMIC BOOK, THREE STORIES. WELCOME TO THE DOGHOUSE ISSUE SIX.

"WE'VE GOT A HELL OF A NEW JOB FOR YOU. IF YOU WANT IT."

Spider returns! Following the prison incident Holloway and MacGregor recruit some brains to go with their muscle - in SPIDER.

"SO YOU GUYS HAVE REALLY NEVER MET ANYONE FROM THE FLIPSIDE BEFORE? WEIRD."

Saffron brings the gang up to speed on the world that's just come crashing in, with some shocking revelations! - in FLIPSIDE.

"MAKES YOU KILL FOR IT... OR GET KILLED. IT FEEDS OFF IT... AND IT'S HUNGRY."

Something has settled in New Barrington and it's not leaving until every last soul is dead - in POPULATION ZERO.
name: Spider; Flipside; Population Zero

description: Dorian is up for the fight of his life when Basil is off to get his revenge. All of this plus high school finals.

A behind the scenes preview of the hit comic seres featuring Batman legend Eartha Kitt. Eartha Kitt is on holiday, searching for the purrfect wave. When suddenly??? Well we won't spoil the surprise. But in the tradition of DC Nation and all good things for all ages comes Eartha Meets The Gorgon, the first in a series of adventures done with the blessing of the legendary actress/singer's estate. Written by New York Times Bestselling Author Marc Shapiro, Eartha Meets The Gorgon is the long anticipated return to good clean fun.

Demon Outside the Bottle

Endstone is the story of a family of stoners... beings who can wield or "rock" mysterious stones that grant unique powers.

Kyri Thunderhead is a simple, martial-arts-dealing deer from the forests of Pennsylvania. Her mate, Jon Montaine, is a powerful stoner with a sordid past. Their daughter, Colindra, is a terrible dragon with a flair for fashion. And Pablo Montaine, the old patriarch of the clan, is literally the skeleton in the family closet.

Together, and sometimes apart, they must keep the Banestone, and the evil god-like being that dwells within it, from destroying the world. But is it a world worth saving?
name: Demon Outside the Bottle

description: Falling Rock National Park is a comic strip that takes place in a southwestern national park. Park Ranger Dee looks after animal residents Carver, Ernesto, Pam, and Melissa. Funny and sweet, Falling Rock is a pleasant place to visit.

Do you dare to enter the Burlesque Theater of Blood? A brand new tale by regular artist Sergio Calvet, features Lucy and Morlack teaming up to stop a deadly troupe of curvy cannibals! Who will survive? What will be left of them? And how much clothing will they be wearing? Find out this issue!

Also, because you demanded it, the origin of Halloween Man! Superstar artists Nicola Scott (Earth 2) and David Baldeon (Marvel Zombies Christmas Carol) bring you a look at how it all began!

Finally, we dig up the cult-classic "Blood God of Virtual Beach." Penciled by Benjamin Hall (Dead@17) this killer story of sun, surfing and fish monsters will rock your socks off. All this and more, this issue of Halloween Man!

Based on the hit videogame INFINITE CRISIS! Having survived the destruction of an entire universe, Batman, Nightmare Robin, Arcane Green Lantern and Gaslight Catwoman arrive on the home world of Atomic Wonder Woman. In this devastated, post-apocalyptic landscape, the team finally confronts Atomic Two-Face and his mutant hordes, commanded by the fearsome Atomic Bane.

volume.name: Infinite Crisis: Fight For the Multiverse

description: As Sinestro manipulates both friend and foe, Hal Jordan battles Guy Gardner and the showdown between Superman and Ganthet begins. It all builds to a final climax in this penultimate issue of Year Two!
name: Crashing to Earth

volume.name: Injustice: Gods Among Us Year Two

description:
Suspension Of A Public Service

The ticket that exploded.
name: Suspension Of A Public Service

description: Now outside their Meka, Onoo and Llamas trek through the ruins of the city they originally set out to protect. Survival becomes a matter of life and death, especially when encountered by a band of not-too-happy displaced civilians!

At the end of the world…! The alien visitors are appearing all around the planet and our last hope lies with Alden Baylor, who shares a special connection with one of the alien hosts. Will Alden be able to keep the peace between a desperate government and the powerful invaders, or is mankind doomed to extinction? The thrilling conclusion to the critically acclaimed story by writer Jeff Parker, artist Sandy Jarrell, and colorist Kevin Volo!

The second volume of Box Brown's new ongoing anthology series, Number! This includes two new stories, "Sk8rh8r" and "Elroy Mirrors' Big Score". In "Sk8rh8r", 33-year-old Rose skateboards drunk to grab some delicious burgers and runs into both Crazy Bob and the police, while in "Elroy Mirrors' Big Score", Elroy tries to build his documentary film career while dealing with his more successful friends, the strange subjects of his films, and his direction in life.
name: Sk8rh8r; Elroy Mirrors' Big Score

description: After being overcome with emotions from the lost of his first friend, an alley rat, a mysterious power wells up inside the young street urchin, Oops, and a major magical blast erupts from within him! Knocked unconscious, he wakes to see a giant figure looming over him. What trouble has Oops gotten himself into now?

Loopy cleric Bish Bathenwell leads his followers in an assault on the Temple of Crwm, unfortunately it turns out that it has already been booked for a private funtion that evening. Later, Bish and Pewfell are sacrificed to Crwm, the wyrm-god, as he begins his thousand-year reign of terror over the world.

Avast, ye mateys! Pirates on the horizon—and zombies off the starboard bow! Follow young, time-traveling adventurers Nate and Patrice as they take to the seas to steal from the notoriously notorious dread Pirate Chestbeard! Our heroes must thwart Zomboss's nefarious schemes and protect all eras of humanity by recovering the time-scattered parts to the zombie leader’s wicked Sun Vacuum. And of course the last Sun Vacuum piece is with the notoriously notorious dread Pirate Chestbeard! Prepare yourself for the fifth thrilling installment of Plants vs. Zombies: Timepocalypse by Paul Tobin (Bandette, Prometheus) and Ron Chan (The Guild, Husbands)!

The penultimate chapter of Dark Horse Digital’s second run of Plants vs. Zombies comics!

A “fun-dead” adventure through time!

SHARK FIGHT! PIRATES! ZOMBIES!

“YARRR, YARRR, YARRR! ”—Pirate Chestbeard

In this issue, Nate and Patrice go back in time to Eye Island, where the Pirate Chestbeard has buried one of the missing sun vacuum parts.

They battle a shark and travel to the island. Nate and some plants battle Zomboss's forces whole Patrice outwits Chestbeard's pirates, and once again they manage to get the machine part.

The class Ski Trip is here! Zack and Slater are both counting on a romantic snowy backdrop to ask out Kelly out. But when Kelly doesn’t have enough money for the trip, Zack sets her up with a job—modeling ski ware on the slopes, all expenses paid! Has Zack finally won Kelly’s affections, or will he get the cold shoulder? And where’d Screech disappear to?!

The end is here! With the Ultimate League of Ultimate Justice on the brink of defeat, can Maxwell scribble his way out of this one and save the universe? Or will the Anti-Monitor finish the story by erasing him once and for all? Find out in our final issue!
name: The Ultimate Battle of Ultimate Finality

volume.name: Scribblenauts Unmasked: A Crisis of Imagination

description: Diana Prince's heroics continue! Wonder Woman faces her greatest peril as the Gods' gifts are withdrawn one by one. And since their first gift was life, how far will her unraveling go? Then, learn how Diana earned the twin bracelets that protect her from the bullets of Man's World!
name: Taketh Away; Brace Yourself

description: Diana’s gifts are slowly deserting her, but things aren’t as dire as they appear, and help is coming from a most unanticipated quarter!
name: Taketh Away, Part 2 of 2

description: The Manhunters are closer to Earth's destruction, forcing Lois to team up with Clark as well as with an unlikely character--Lex. But can they trust him?
name: Chapter Four

description: Les “Survivorman” Stroud’s abilities are continually tested as his pursuit of the Horn of Providence leads him to the English Moors. Les, his son Logan, and sidekick Cro Magnon face wolves, severe weather, and a rotating cast of villain Oswald Good’s “assistants.”

Waypoint

Hunted by the Wex, Caillo learns her fate.
name: Waypoint

volume.name: Tales From The Grey Earth: The Wex

description:
The classic 1950's space adventures are back! Tom Corbett, Roger Manning, and Astro were attending Space Academy, in a TV series that sparked novels, comic strips, and merchandise. This edition is from January 1954, "Spaceship Graveyard": While patrolling the Saturn run the Polaris is wreaked by Space Junk and the cadets float to a planetoid with a magnetic graveyard.

NOTE: This book is a reprinted archive title with some visual distortion.

Having been exposed to the supernatural world around her, FBI agent Alicia Hardwicke finds herself drawn deeper into the dark mystery surrounding the legendary bounty hunter: John Tower.

Obsessed with discovering his many secrets, she confronts Tower's most trusted confidant, Romulus Barnes, and unveils the unsettling origins of their partnership.

Meanwhile, after being defeated at their last encounter, The Brotherhood of the Rose uncover a weakness of Tower's as they plot their next move against him...

Note: The digital edition (9/17/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Phantom Starfighters

In the timeless expanse of the universe, there are two constants that exist, Good and Evil, and Life and Death, both conducting their endless symphony throughout space, as it has always been since time began.

Life and death struggles, whether they be born from nature, or caused by the maliciousness of war, are but a test issued to all beings, making and labeling us all heroes, villains, and cowards... Linking everyone in a desperate battle for survival.

In the year 3020, on a remote outpost orbiting mars, such a battle is about to begin against an overwhelming, opposing force, possessing advanced alien weaponry. The occupants of the Omega 3 Space Station are about to experience first hand the galactic constants of Good and Evil, and Life and Death. Their chances of survival... Slim. But amid the inconceivable carnage and destruction that will ensue, a Hero will rise, and a Legend will be born... Colonel Jennifer Rocket.

name: Phantom Starfighters

description: The groundbreaking digital comic returns! Half a million downloads, and the inspiration for everything from Thrillbent itself to comics like Moth City! Read where it all began! Valentine flees from eerie, red-eyed cossacks with the bundle given to him by the dying General. Wounded, cornered... Valentine opens the bundle. And things get very strange, very fast.

Hulkamania is running wild, bruther! With the clock ticking for Daniel Bryan, Rey Mysterio, and CM Punk to uncover who or what caused them to go berserk at a Monday Night Raw taping, the Superstars have one last hope to save them from being fired by Mr. McMahon-- the immortal Hulk Hogan. The Hulkster may hold the key to proving their innocence but first they're going to have to save him from the wrath of "The Animal" Batista!
name: Haze of Glory!: Conclusion

person_credits.name: Eiichiro Oda
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, inker, cover

description: Space as we know it is a mysterious void waiting to be explored. The chain of command on our planet always has humans at the top of the list... That list is about to be revised.

volume.name: Above Us Only Sky: The Beginning

description: When Mom and Dad are out and away, Betty and Veronica come to play! The girls are coming over to babysit in this new 100-page digital exclusive. Taking care of kids isn’t so easy, though—can Betty and Veronica handle some of Riverdale’s unruliest kids? You’ll have so much fun reading this book, you won’t even notice your parents have left!
Join Benedict Barlow, a washed up Paranormal Investigator, and his trusty sidekick, Timothy as they track an explosion of violent incidents through the small town of Rotwood.

volume.name: Benedict Barlow & The Curse of Rotwood

description:
In the city of Heistburg, you're on the take or you're taken out. Guns are out, but crime is in and when you come to this town, you'd better fit in. The only law is that there is loyalty among the gangs of the 'Burg.

Trust is everything to liars, cheats and thieves.

Chapter 1

It's the 1930's. The performers of the world's most sought after circus find themselves in the sights of a military force known as 'The Storm'. The Storm's goal: A new world order.
name: Chapter 1

description:
Saints and Sinners

Every story has a beginning but sometimes there is a story before the beginning. Find out how this generations guardians came to be.
name: Saints and Sinners

description: This surreal adventure from the creator of Dog Boy and Bughouse serves up Lucha Libre wrestlers and an ancient vampire who prefers chicken. Two expats move to remote Oaxaca, the fabled highland city in southern Mexico. Rex, earnest yet duplicitous, flees from mid-life crisis and fear of death. Beautiful Gertie, cynical but honest, is just plain bored and craves adventure.

Constantly wallowing in her comfy bed with her cat, while watching TV and eating snacks, seems pretty great to Debbie. Until her room starts flooding with a strange liquid and Debbie is too lazy to escape! Luckily, her cat finally admits it can talk and leads Debbie through a modern Inferno, on a spiritual quest through Debbie's personal states of mind.

Eleanor, beautiful red-haired witch. I'll give you a kiss so you'll never forget this day-or me.... Eleanor has come to the kingdom of Quaram as an English tutor for the royal family. At the royal party she's invited to, on her twenty-first birthday, she's asked to dance by Jasim, the kingdom's second prince. His gorgeous black hair, his hungry eyes...in that dreamlike moment spent in his embrace, she falls for him before she realizes it. But little does Eleanor know, even as Jasim passionately proclaims his love for her, he has a dreadful scheme in mind...!
name: Vol. 1

description: Harriet, an antique dealer, buys a mountain villa in a village in Southern France to enjoy her summer vacation with her niece. But the mountain villa is an abysmal abandoned house?! And what surprises her more is the fact that the former owner of the mountain villa was her ex-lover, Andre. He was the man who captured her eighteen-year-old heart and sent her into fits of despair. The love and hatred she buried eight years ago comes back to life and tortures her emotions!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Fubo: Dog of the Future

A scientist creates a robot dog with unexpected results.
name: Fubo: Dog of the Future

description:
EYE OF THE GODS is a psychological thriller about a man whose life spirals out of control when he is cursed with the ability of remote viewing.

It combines the high-tension paranoia of ENEMY OF THE STATE with the foreboding chill of THE DEAD ZONE. Sean Black undergoes surgery, cloning his eyes to restoring his failing vision. After the operation, he "dreams" of a murder, only to discover that it really happened... ...But the death isn't being reported as a crime. When his curiosity gets the best of him, Sean uncovers a conspiracy and sets off a chain of events that unravel his life.
name: GN

description:
Don't let the controversy of her later personal life fool you, Liza Minnelli was once the most respected star of the musical theatre stage. Her signature role as the rough, sexy Sally Bowles in Cabaret defined a uniquely Broadway style, catapulted her to the top of the musical charts, and solidified her position in the pantheon of live performers. Special cover by famed artist Keaton Alexander Kohl.

FUBAR: By the Sword goes medieval on the walking dead with stories of ye olde zombie-stomping madness! This TPB compiles the two issue mini-series.
name: TPB

description: A wrenching romance comic of married passions.
To prove himself a man, Bobby Rockwell becomes a guinea pig for the Immense Robot Test Program.

Grandpa's Tale

Grandpa rabbit begins telling his fantastic tale of adventure, beginning with his meeting of an important ally, and some strange creatures.
name: Grandpa's Tale

description: Dark forces are conspiring to prevent humankind from reaching its true potential. Thankfully, as newly appointed 'Protector of the Realm,' Agent Matthew Dee uses his skills as a covert spy and Combat Mage to ensure America's freedom from the grip of evil. Written by True Blood actor Michael McMillian and illustrated by newcomer Anna Wieszczyk, Lucid is Archaia's first title published in association with Zachary Quinto (Star Trek) and his company, Before the Door.
name: Volume One

description: Fay is a sweet and simple nurse. One day a famous movie director, Lew, proposes to her after meeting her for the first time. Lew tells Fay that he doesn't believe in love, and he only wants to get married because he is tired of living alone. Lew asks Fay to be a good wife, and nothing more. Somehow, Fay is attracted to Lew and decides to marry him. Fay is just about to enter the gaudy Hollywood life as a newlywed!
name: Vol. 1

description: Journey with the Wandering Stars - seven mathematicians from various eras in history mysteriously banded together to solve problems of a grand and metaphysical nature. These first two tales feature an angry abstract artist who steals the vanishing point from all of reality and the Invisible Hand who is attempting to log the Philosopher Forest with his Seven Deadly Sins.

volume.name: Mathemagick: The Point and the Invisible Hand

description:
Snow Fall

Max Hunter is a cyber cowboy bounty hunter cleaning the streets of Gateway city from the scum that reside in it. Max is chasing down his next bounty when he finds he's not the only one. Vincent Snow is an assassin who has set his sights on Max's bounty. Now Max has to try to stop snow and try to save his bounty. The conflict between Max and Snow begins here in Max Hunter; Snow Fall!
name: Snow Fall: Part 1

description: My Geek Family is an all-ages story of the misadventures of a family of geeks. This story follows the day in the life of a family who wear their geekiness on their sleeves (sometimes literally). Meet Doug and Tina, the parents of two young boys named Owen and Dylan, and spend a typical Saturday with them. Everyone is a geek about something, you just have to be passionate about what you like.
